definition.value: A member of the class of oxanes that is oxane which is substituted by a formyl group at position 2 and an acetyloxy group at position 3.

A member of the class of 7-hydroxyisoflavones that is 3-phenyl-4H-chromen-4-one which is substituted by a hydroxy group at position 7 and chloro groups at positions 2' and 4'. It is a SIRT1 activator.
An ultra long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is the all-trans-isomer of octaprenol.
A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is the all-trans-isomer of hexaprenol.
A hex-3-en-1-ol in which the double bond adopts an E-configuration.
An alkyl caffeate ester that is a alkyl caffeate ester.
A biphenyl that has four hydroxy groups attached to the benzenoid ring system (position 2,2',3 and 3'); majos species at pH 7.3
A member of the class of phenols that is phenol which is substituted by a propyl group at position 2.
A member of the class of catechols that is catechol which is substituted by a propyl group at position 3. It is a chemical component in tobacco.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of 2-hydroxy-6-oxonona-2,4-dienoic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A phosphatidylinositol anion where the inositol is either not phosphorylated or phosphorylated at position 4 and/or position 5; major species at pH 7.3.
A phosphatidylinositol anion where the inositol is phosphorylated at position 3 and either phosphorylated or not at position 4 and/or position 5; major species at pH 7.3.
A polyprenol comprising of eight prenyl units with a terminal hydroxy group.
A polyprenol comprising of six prenyl units with a terminal hydroxy group.
A 3-prenylated cyclized Trp residue found in Kawaguchipeptin A, a cyclic undecapeptide isolated from the cyanobacterium Microcystis aeruginosa (see article DOI=10.1016/0040-4020(96)00452-8)
An alpha,beta-unsaturated monocarboxylic acid that is nona-2,4-dienoic acid carrying hydroxy and oxo substituents at positions 2 and 6 respectively.
A hydroperoxy fatty acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of any (2R)-hydroperoxy fatty acid.

A member of the class of nectriapyrones that is 2H-pyran-2-one which is substituted at positions 3, 4, 5 and 6 by methyl, hydroxy, methyl and but-2-en-2-yl groups, respectively. It is a secondary metabolite produced by Aspergillus fumigatus and inhibits germination of spores of the inducing Streptomyces rapamycinicus.

A branched amino pentasaccharide comprising a linear chain of alpha-sialyl, beta-D-galactosyl, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl and N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl residues, linked (2->3), (1->4) and (1->3) respectively, with an alpha-L-fucosyl residue linked to the N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residue.
Any hydroperoxy fatty acid in which the hydroperoxy group is located on the carbon at position 2.
Any 2-hydroperoxy fatty acid which has R configuration at the carbon bearing the hydroperoxy group.
Any 2-hydroperoxy fatty acid which has S configuration at the carbon bearing the hydroperoxy group.

A secondary carboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of N-[(benzyloxy)carbonyl]-O-tert-butyl-L-serine with the primary amino group of ethyl (2E,4S)-5-[(3S)-2-oxopyrrolidin-3-yl]-4-(L-phenylalanylamino)pent-2-enoate. It is a potent enterovirus 3C protease inhibitor with EC50 of 180 nM against enterovirus 71 (EV71) and 60 nM against human rhinovirus 14 in a live virus-cell-based assay.

A member of the class of fluoren-9-ones that is 9H-fluoren-9-one which is substituted by a 2-(diethylamino)ethoxy group at positions 2 and 7. It is an interferon inducer and a selective alpha7 nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (alpha7 nAChR) agonist. Its hydrochloride salt is used as an antiviral drug.

A peptide zwitterion that is the dizwitterionic form of angiotensin I having both carboxy groups deprotonated and the aspartyl amino group and arginine side-chain protonated. It is the major species at pH 7.3.

A peptide zwitterion that is the dizwitterionic form of angiotensin (1-9) having both carboxy groups deprotonated and the aspartyl amino group and arginine side-chain protonated. It is the major species at pH 7.3.
A peptide cation obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group and protonation of the primary amino and guanidino groups of [des-Phe(8), des-Arg(9)]-bradykinin. It is the major species at pH 7.3.
Candidate tetrodotoxin biosynthetic intermediate isolated from the Okinawan newt Cynops ensicauda popei in Kudo et al. 2014

An azaspiro compound resulting from the spiro-fusion of 2-imino-1,3-diazinan-4-one at position 6 with 1,3-dimethylcyclohexane. It is a marine metabolite isolated from Vietnamese pufferfish Tetraodon biocellatus and a potential intermediate in the biosynthetic pathway leading to the synthesis of tetrodotoxin.
An ammonium ion derivative resulting from the protonation of the two tertiary amino groups of tilorone.
The dihydrochloride salt of tilorone. It is used as an antiviral drug to treat influenza, herpes infection, viral hepatitis, acute respiratory viral infections and SARS.

A member of the class of oxazolidines that is 1,3-oxazolidine which is substituted by two methyl groups, dichloroacetyl group and a methyl group at positions 2, 3 and 5, respectively. It is a herbicide safener.
A 2-[4-methyl-5-oxo-4-(propan-2-yl)-4,5-dihydro-1H-imidazol-2-yl]quinoline-3-carboxylic acid that has R-configuration. It is the more active enantiomer of imazaquin.
A 2-[4-methyl-5-oxo-4-(propan-2-yl)-4,5-dihydro-1H-imidazol-2-yl]quinoline-3-carboxylic acid that has S-configuration.
A quinolinemonocarboxylic acid that is quinoline-3-carboxylic acid which is substituted by a 4-methyl-5-oxo-4-(propan-2-yl)-4,5-dihydro-1H-imidazol-2-yl group at position 2.

A peptide cation obtained from the deprotonation of the carboxy groups of L-alpha-glutamyl and L-leucine residues, and protonation of the side chains of L-lysyl and L-arginyl residues of neurotensin. It is the major species at pH 7.3.

A peptide cation obtained from the deprotonation of the carboxy groups of L-alpha-glutamyl and L-isoleucine residues, and protonation of the side chains of L-lysyl and L-arginyl residues of neurotensin (1-12). It is the major species at pH 7.3.

A peptide cation obtained from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of L-leucine residue, and protonation of the amino group of L-isoleucyl and protonation of the side chains of L-arginyl residues of kinetensin. It is the major species at pH 7.3.

A peptide cation obtained from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of L-phenylalanine residue, and protonation of the amino group of L-isoleucyl and protonation of the side chains of L-arginyl residues of kinetensin (1-8). It is the major species at pH 7.3.

A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-imazapic. It is a selective imidazolinone herbicide for pre- and post-emergent control of some annual and perennial grasses and broadleaf weeds. It kills plants by inhibiting the activity of the enzyme acetohydroxy acid synthase (AHAS).
A 5-methyl-2-[4-methyl-5-oxo-4-(propan-2-yl)-4,5-dihydro-1H-imidazol-2-yl]pyridine-3-carboxylic acid that has (R)-configuration.
